ivardefs.name: city
ivardefs.desc: The name of the city, town, suburb, village or other community or delivery center.

ivardefs.name: country
ivardefs.desc: Country - a nation as commonly understood or generally accepted.

ivardefs.name: district
ivardefs.desc: The name of the administrative area (county).

ivardefs.name: line_
ivardefs.desc: This component contains the house number, apartment number, street name, street direction,  P.O. Box number, delivery hints, and similar address information.

ivardefs.name: period
ivardefs.desc: Time period when address was/is in use.

ivardefs.name: postalCode
ivardefs.desc: A postal code designating a region defined by the postal service.

ivardefs.name: state
ivardefs.desc: Sub-unit of a country with limited sovereignty in a federally organized country. A code may be used if codes are in common use (e.g. US 2 letter state codes).

ivardefs.name: text
ivardefs.desc: Specifies the entire address as it should be displayed e.g. on a postal label. This may be provided instead of or as well as the specific parts.

ivardefs.name: type
ivardefs.desc: Distinguishes between physical addresses (those you can visit) and mailing addresses (e.g. PO Boxes and care-of addresses). Most addresses are both.

properties.desc: Base StructureDefinition for Address Type: An address expressed using postal conventions (as opposed to GPS or other location definition formats).  This data type may be used to convey addresses for use in delivering mail as well as for visiting locations
